{[%evp 0,43,19,31,14,-14,-11,0,0,-14,14,14,-2,-3,26,16,8,13,11,14,5,5,43,-13,23,15,14,-2,8,-9,10,19,13,4,22,5,26,-13,40,-31,10,6,6,6,24,-4]} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. g3 Be7 5. Bg2 O-O 6. O-O c6 7. Qc2 Nbd7 8. Nbd2 b6 9. e4 dxe4 {This move was played in more than 2000 games. It's a move with a lot of historical games, but nowadays, it's clear that this is not the best way for Black.} 10. Nxe4 Nxe4 (10... Bb7 {Is more popular, but it's even worse.} 11. Nxf6+ Nxf6 12. Rd1 $1 {[%cal Rc6c5] We prevent c5.} Qc8 (12... Qc7 {allows} 13. Bf4 Bd6 14. Bxd6 Qxd6 15. c5 $16 {[%csl Rb7] Famous dream position for White. Just look at Black's bishop on b7.}) 13. Re1 $1 {Another strong prophylactic move against c5.} (13. c5 {is also fine.}) 13... Re8 {Black defends the bishop with the idea to play c5, but we can play} (13... c5 $2 14. d5 $1 $16 {[%csl Re7][%cal Ge1e7]}) 14. c5 $1 $16 {[%csl Rb7]}) 11. Qxe4 Bb7 {[%cal Gd7f6,Yc6c5] Black is ready for Nf6, followed by c5.} 12. Rd1 (12. Re1 $5 {deserves attention.}) 12... Qc8 $1 {[%cal Gc6c5] This is Black's best chance: he prepares c6-c5, but at the same time doesn't place the queen on c7, where it would become a target for our Bf4 move.} (12... Nf6 {Black's most common move, but after} 13. Qc2 {we transpose in 10...Bb7.}) (12... Qc7 $2 13. Bf4 $1 Bd6 14. Bxd6 Qxd6 15. c5 $1 $16 {[%csl Rb7]}) 13. Bf4 {[%cal Gf3e5] We prepare Ne5 so that after Nxe5, we can recapture with the bishop.} (13. Ne5 Nxe5 14. dxe5 Qc7 $11) 13... c5 $1 {Black needs to play c5 right now.} (13... Re8 $2 14. Ne5 Nxe5 15. Bxe5 $16 {[%csl Rb7]}) (13... Nf6 $2 14. Qe2 Re8 {Now, White has another fantastic prophylactic move against c5:} (14... c5 15. d5 $16 {[%csl Re7]}) 15. Bh3 $1 $16 {[%csl Rc8][%cal Gh3c8]} c5 $2 16. d5 $1 $18 {[%csl Re6][%cal Gh3e6]}) 14. d5 Re8 $1 {Black doesn't need to rush playing Bf6.} (14... Bf6 $6 {[%csl Rf6] The bishop on f6 looks great, but in fact, it will be a target for the Nd2-Ne4 idea.} 15. Qc2 exd5 16. cxd5 Re8 17. Nd2 $16 {[%cal Gd2e4,Yd2c4] Ne4 or Nc4 next.}) 15. Qc2 (15. Qd3 $5 {is also possible, but it's not clear where White's queen is better placed.}) 15... exd5 16. cxd5 h6 $1 {[%cal Rf3g5] Was played only once, but it's Black continuation. The priority is to prevent all Ng5 ideas.} (16... Bf6 $6 {Black's most common move, but not the best.} 17. Nd2 $14 {[%csl Rf6]}) (16... Nf6 $2 17. Ng5 $18 {[%csl Rh7][%cal Gf4e5]}) 17. Rac1 {[%cal Yb2b4] Sometimes we can think about b2-b4.} Bf8 18. Bh3 Qd8 19. b4 $14 {Black's position is not bad, but we still have some pressure, and the position is new.} *

