{[%evp 0,13,27,28,19,18,17,12,20,0,5,5,11,10,11,-3]} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. g3 Be7 5. Bg2 O-O 6. O-O dxc4 7. Qc2 b6 {This move is very popular nowadays.} (7... c5 {[%csl Rc8] This move is a principled move from the strategic perspective. The only problem for Black is that it will be difficult to develop his bishop on c8.} 8. dxc5 Bxc5 9. Qxc4 Qe7 $1 {This is Black's best continuation, and my recommendation is} 10. Rd1 $5 {A move that was played only once. We will check it in "Position 1" of this Unit.}) (7... c6 {This move has a very solid reputation.} 8. a4 $5 {This is my recommendation. I don't want to say that 8.a4 is stronger than 8.Qxc4, but there are much fewer games, and it's easier to surprise our opponent.} (8. Qxc4 {Is by far White's most common continuation, but a lot of games here, and you can check the model game So-Mamedyarov, Candidates 2018.}) 8... b6 {This looks as Black's most logical continuation, and now we will play} 9. Na3 $5 {[%csl Yc4][%cal Ga3c4] My idea is to capture on c4 with the knight. We will check it in "Position 2" of this Unit.}) 8. Bg5 {This is my recommendation.} (8. Ne5 {I don't like this direction because it gets too concrete after} Qxd4 9. Bxa8 Qxe5 $44 {Black needs to play some best moves, but he will be fine. In my opinion, if your opponent plays 7...b6, then for sure he is well parepared against 8.Ne5, that's why I don't want to enter in this line.}) 8... Nd5 9. Bxe7 Qxe7 10. Nbd2 {Now, Black has three options.} b5 {This is probably Black's best continuation, but not all players are ready to play it. My idea will be to play} (10... Bb7 {Bb7 is a normal move, but the good thing for us is that it's not so concrete.} 11. Nxc4 Nd7 12. a3 $1 {[%cal Rd5b4,Ge2e4] We stop Nb4 and we are ready for e4. We will check it in "Position 3" of this Unit.}) (10... Ba6 {[%csl Ya6] Black's bishop on a6 might be more active than on b7.} 11. Nxc4 c5 12. Rac1 {is my recommendation, and we will check it in "Position 4" of this Unit.}) 11. h4 $5 h6 12. b3 {[%cal Yc4b3,Yc4c3] Only one game was played here, and we will check this in "Position 5" of this Unit. Black's two options are 12...c3 and 12...cxb3.} *

