{[%evp 0,33,20,20,35,15,15,24,24,-6,6,10,15,15,8,-19,-3,-7,19,19,19,19,22,9,9,30,5,14,14,21,39,43,39,49,61,40]} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. g3 Be7 5. Bg2 O-O 6. O-O dxc4 7. Qc2 b6 8. Bg5 Nd5 (8... Ba6 {Usually, it transposes in the mainline, but Black has two additional options.} 9. Nbd2 Nd5 (9... c3 $6 $146 {Nobody has played it, but I want to check it:} 10. bxc3 Bxe2 11. Rfe1 {White has huge compensation. For example:} Ba6 (11... Bxf3 12. Nxf3 $1 c6 13. Ne5 Qc7 14. c4 $16 {[%csl Rb8]}) 12. Ne5 c6 13. Rad1 $16 {[%csl Rb8,Yc6][%cal Ge5c6,Rb8d7] Black cannot play Nd7.}) (9... b5 $6 $146 {This is also dubious and has never been played, but it's always better to know what to do against b5.} 10. Ne5 Nd5 11. Bxe7 Qxe7 12. a4 $5 (12. b3 $5 $14 {also possible.}) 12... c6 13. axb5 (13. Be4 $5 {I am not sure about this move.}) 13... cxb5 14. b3 Rc8 15. bxc4 bxc4 16. Nexc4 $14 {Looks unpleasant for Black.}) 10. Bxe7 Qxe7 11. Nxc4 {transposes to the mainline.}) 9. Bxe7 Qxe7 10. Nbd2 Ba6 {[%csl Ya6] Compared to 10...Bb7, sometimes Black's bishop on a6 might be more active.} 11. Nxc4 c5 {standard move.} (11... Nd7 12. Rfd1 c5 13. Qa4 $14) 12. Rac1 {This is my recommendation.} (12. dxc5 Rc8 $132 {Black's play is more simple.}) (12. Rfc1 $5 {Also deserves attention. You can check the model game Rapport-Huzman, 2018.} Nd7 (12... Rc8 $6 {this move is not so good anymore, for concrete reasons} 13. e4 Nb4 14. Qb3 cxd4 15. a3 N4c6 16. e5 $14 {Probably the difference with the 12.Rac1 variation is that our rook is on a1 and not on f1, and this means that it will not be a target for Black's Ba6 in some variation.}) 13. Qa4 Bb7 14. Qa3 $14 {Rapport-Huzman, 2018.}) 12... Rc8 {This is the most logical move.} 13. Qd2 $5 $146 {[%csl Rc2,Gd2][%cal Rd5b4,Rc8c2] This is my recommendation. Our idea is to move the queen from c2, where it is a target for Black's rook on c8, or for the Nb4 ideas.} (13. Nce5 Nd7 $1 $146 {the best for Black.} (13... f6 $6 {looks antipositional.} 14. Nd3 Nd7 15. Qa4 $16 {[%csl Re6] White is better.}) 14. Qa4 Bxe2 15. Qxd7 Qxd7 16. Nxd7 Bxf1 17. Kxf1 cxd4 18. Rb1 $13 {we need to save our rook. We can take the d4 pawn, but I think Black is fine in this endgame.}) (13. e4 Nb4 14. Qb3 cxd4 $132 {is good for Black.}) 13... Nd7 (13... Nc6 14. dxc5 bxc5 15. b3 $14 {White is slightly better, thanks to the more pleasant structure.}) 14. b3 {[%csl Yc4][%cal Gb3c4] We protect the knight} Bb7 15. e4 N5f6 16. e5 {Looks slightly better for White.} Ne8 17. Qf4 $14 *

