{[%evp 0,41,28,19,19,17,20,12,20,-5,5,5,10,10,5,-4,-3,-11,14,14,14,20,32,-39,6,6,6,6,5,5,5,5,5,9,20,12,24,0,0,0,0,0,0,-5]} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. g3 Be7 5. Bg2 O-O 6. O-O dxc4 7. Qc2 b6 {we have two serious options} 8. Bg5 Nd5 9. Bxe7 Qxe7 10. Nbd2 b5 {This is probably Black's best continuation, but not all players are ready to play it.} 11. h4 $5 {[%cal Gf3g5] my recommendation. We are ready for Ng5.} (11. b3 {is White's most common continuation, but after} cxb3 12. Nxb3 a5 13. Ne5 c6 14. Rfc1 a4 15. Nc5 {Black can play} f6 16. Ned3 $44 {White has a good compensation, but Black has an improved version of our mainline.}) 11... h6 {[%csl Yg5][%cal Yh6g5,Rf3g5] This is Black's most logical move, but now we have an improved version of the 11.b3 move.} (11... Bb7 {was played in the game Gschnitzer-Lohia.} 12. b3 c5 13. bxc4 bxc4 14. dxc5 Nd7 15. e4 N5f6 {and White missed the strong} 16. e5 $1 Nd5 17. Rfb1 $16 {White has a very big advantage.}) 12. b3 c3 {This is the most critical continuation, in my opinion.} (12... cxb3 13. Nxb3 a5 14. Ne5 c6 15. Rfc1 Rd8 16. Nc5 $14 {[%cal Rf7f6] Do you remember the same position without h6-h4 included? (11.b3 variation). Here, Black can no longer play the move f7-f6 because of Ng6. That's why I think that h4-h6 is a good inclusion for us.}) 13. e4 cxd2 14. exd5 exd5 15. Qxd2 Qd6 16. Rac1 $44 {Black's position is not so terrible, but of course we have a good compensation, and it's not so pleasant to play from the Black's side.} a5 {Black's most logical move.} 17. Ne5 (17. Rfe1 $5 {also possible}) 17... a4 $5 {was probably the best.} (17... Bf5 $2 {was played in the game Grebnev-Ohanyan, 2024.} 18. Rc5 c6 19. Qf4 Qf6 {And now, White missed} 20. Rfc1 $1 Ra6 21. g4 Be6 22. Qxf6 gxf6 23. Nxc6 $16 {Black needs to defend a very bad endgame.}) 18. Rc5 {[%csl Rd6]} c6 19. Rfc1 Bb7 20. R5c3 $5 (20. Qf4 $5 $44 {We have compensation and some initiative.} Nd7 $2 {is not possible because of} 21. Rxc6 $1 $18) 20... axb3 21. axb3 $36 {[%csl Rb7][%cal Rb8d7,Ge5c6,Yg2h3] Whenever Black plays Nd7, we can take on c6. We can also consider the Bh3 idea radically stopping Black's development. Of course, if you play against an engine, you will not win, but in a real game, we can put a lot of pressure on our opponent and wait for his mistake.} *

