{[%evp 0,52,27,27,27,16,7,16,16,0,8,8,15,15,17,-3,31,31,43,43,37,37,37,37,37,35,37,37,37,30,30,15,15,15,12,0,7,28,13,8,9,4,45,43,80,27,43,63,69,69,70,71,72,62,82]} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. g3 Be7 5. Bg2 O-O 6. O-O dxc4 7. Qc2 b5 8. a4 {Recently, the move} Bb7 9. axb5 a6 10. bxa6 Nxa6 11. Qxc4 Bd5 12. Qc3 c5 13. Be3 Ne4 14. Qe1 Nb4 15. Rxa8 Qxa8 16. Nc3 Nc2 {is more risky, for the engine is the same, but over the board it is harder.} 17. Nxd5 $1 {is a very strong move.} exd5 {is the best response.} ({After} 17... Qxd5 $6 18. Qc1 $1 {the opposition on the long diagonal might get pretty annoying.} Nxe3 {was played in the game Deac-Yoo.} (18... cxd4 19. Bf4 {[%csl Rc2,Rd5] Equal material now, but we have two bishops.} d3 $1 $146 {is the only move.} (19... Qb3 $2 {Also loses a piece.} 20. Ne1 $1 Nxe1 21. Bxe4 f5 22. Bb1 $18 {[%csl Re1] 1-0 (39) Royal,S (2375)-Prokofiev,V (2279) Miercurea Ciuc 2022} Bb4 23. Bd2 $18) (19... Rc8 $4 20. Ne1 $18 {[%csl Yc2,Ye4] Black loses material.}) 20. exd3 Qxd3 21. Ne5 {Despite the equal material, White's bishop pair as well as the unstable black pieces give White an edge. A possible line would be} Qe2 22. Qd1 Qxd1 23. Rxd1 f5 {Only move.} 24. Nc6 Bf6 25. b4 Nc3 26. Rd2 Nd4 $1 {Tactical defense.} 27. Kf1 Ndb5 28. h4 $14 {[%csl Yb4][%cal Yf1e1,Ye1d2,Yd2d3,Yd3c4] We can definitely play on.}) 19. Qxe3 cxd4 20. Nxd4 Bc5 21. Qxe4 {We enter the endgame.} Qxe4 22. Bxe4 Bxd4 23. b4 $14 {The endgame is not a draw.} Rb8 24. Rb1 $14 {[%csl Ya6,Yc4][%cal Gb4b5,Ge4c6,Ge2e3,Ya6b6,Yc4c5,Yb5b6,Yb6b7] The position is not guaranteed, it is 50% win and 50% draw, White will try to push for a win for 100 moves, you can imagine one day a king on c4 and a rook on a6 with some exchange saq ideas, it is one plan, other plans also exist. So it is playable.}) (17... Nxe1 $2 18. Nxe7+ Kh8 19. Rxe1 {The position is winning.} Qb7 {Seems to trap the knight, but} 20. Ne5 $1 $18 {[%csl Ge4][%cal Ge7c6,Gg2e4]}) 18. Qc1 {There was a game Deac-Rasulov.} Rc8 {This is Black's best bet on obtaining counterplay.} (18... Nxe3 {was played.} 19. Qxe3 Qb7 20. Ne1 $5 {is simpler, you don't need to know anything.} (20. Rb1 {Normal move, but you need to find a plan after} Rb8 21. h4 $14 {You need to play well, while my recommendation is just auto-pilot, 2 results.}) 20... Qxb2 21. Bxe4 $1 dxe4 22. Qxe4 Bd6 23. dxc5 Bxc5 24. Nd3 $14 {[%csl Rc5,Gd3] 4v3 and knight against bishop.}) 19. Bh3 $5 {seems to be the strongest.} (19. Qxc2 {also possible.} cxd4 20. Qd3 dxe3 21. Qxe3 {Black needs to prove equality.}) 19... Nxe3 20. Qxe3 cxd4 21. Nxd4 $14 {[%csl Rd5][%cal Gb2b3] Again, Black really needs to work to make a draw.} *

