{[%evp 0,39,39,18,23,6,6,7,7,-4,3,21,-6,-2,8,-6,15,20,18,16,71,69,24,34,52,41,39,27,17,18,16,30,15,-21,-14,-28,-34,-28,-7,-32,-20,-40]} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. g3 Be7 5. Bg2 O-O 6. O-O dxc4 7. Qc2 b5 8. a4 b4 9. Nfd2 b3 {b3 is a possible move, but it's very rare and it's unlikely that you will face it.} 10. Qxc4 (10. Qd1 $5 $146 {deserves attention, and you can play it if you just want to have a new and playable position:} Nd5 11. Nxc4 Nc6 $1 {[%cal Ga8b8] Black's priority is to play Rb8.} (11... Ba6 $6 12. Ne5 $1 $16 {[%cal Gb1c3] Nc3 next, this looks better for White.}) 12. Nba3 $5 Rb8 13. e3 $14 {Just a new, playable position, which is slightly better for White.}) 10... Ba6 11. Qxb3 c6 {[%csl Rd4][%cal Gd8d4] Black maintains the option of Qxd4.} (11... Nd5 $6 12. Nc3 $14) 12. Nc3 Qxd4 {necessary move.} (12... Nd5 $2 13. Nf3 $16 {Seriously better for White.}) 13. Nf3 Qb6 14. Qc2 $1 (14. Qxb6 {as played in the game Bosiocic-Nisipeanu, but after} axb6 $11 {The position is just equal.}) 14... Nbd7 {Black needs to complete the development.} (14... Nd5 $6 15. Bg5 $1 $16) 15. Be3 Qb7 $1 {[%cal Gf6d5] Black is ready for Nd5, but we can play} (15... c5 16. a5 Qc7 17. Rfd1 $14) 16. Rfb1 $5 {[%cal Gb2b4]} Nd5 17. Nxd5 cxd5 (17... exd5 $2 18. b4 $16 {White has a big advantage.}) 18. b4 Rfc8 19. Qd1 Bc4 (19... Bxb4 $4 {not possible at least because of} 20. Bd2 Rc4 21. e3 $18 {[%cal Gg2f1] Bf1 next.}) 20. Bd4 $14 ({or} 20. Nd2 $5 Bf6 21. Ra3 $14) *

