{[%evp 0,55,20,20,27,20,23,23,25,-14,0,0,0,0,0,0,49,49,49,34,43,43,44,46,46,27,34,39,78,87,87,87,87,87,84,84,92,100,113,66,66,72,72,69,101,97,113,101,113,119,76,55,47,93,68,113,110,110]} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. g3 Be7 5. Bg2 O-O 6. O-O dxc4 7. Qc2 b5 8. a4 b4 9. Nfd2 Nd5 10. Nxc4 c5 11. dxc5 Bxc5 {This move became possible after the game Pechac-Parkhov, 2022.} 12. e4 Nb6 {only move for Black.} 13. Ncd2 $1 {White's most testing continuation.} (13. e5 Nd5 $11) (13. Rd1 {was also tried, but after} N8d7 14. Nxb6 axb6 15. Nd2 Ba6 16. Nb3 Be7 $11 {Black's position is absolutely fine.}) 13... N8d7 {only move.} (13... Be7 $4 14. a5 $18 {[%cal Yb6d7,Ge4e5] e5 next.}) 14. a5 {Looks fantastic, but the game only started!} Ba6 15. axb6 Rc8 $1 {[%cal Gc5f2] Only move for Black.} (15... Bxf1 $2 16. b7 Rb8 17. Bxf1 Rxb7 18. Nc4 $18 {Black can resign.}) (15... Qxb6 $2 16. Nc4 $18 {Black can resign.}) 16. Qd1 $1 {only move} (16. Rxa6 $4 Bxf2+ $19 {just winning for Black. Warmerdam-Erigaisi, 2022.}) 16... Qxb6 (16... Bxf1 $2 17. b7 $1 $16 {important move: we distract Black's rook from the 'c' file.}) 17. Nb3 Bxf1 (17... Rfd8 $6 {exist opinion that this move is also possible, but I think that after the following concrete line, White is better:} 18. Nxc5 Nxc5 19. Qg4 h5 20. Qf3 Bxf1 21. Bxf1 Nxe4 22. Be3 Qc6 23. Rxa7 Nf6 24. Nd2 Qc2 {Stany-Dushyant, 2023.} 25. Ba6 $1 $146 Rc7 26. Rxc7 Qxc7 27. Qe2 $14 {[%cal Rc7c2,Gd2f3] If Black plays Qc2 we can play Nf3.}) 18. Qxf1 {For human opinion, White is better. We have two bishops, we have material advantage, we can play Ra6 in future (not immediately). But the position is objectively equal} h6 $3 {only move for Black. Without computer, it would be unbelievable to play like this. What is the idea? I don't know, but everybody plays it! Probably it's a prophylactic move against Bf4 because Black could have g5.} (18... Ne5 {looks active, but bad} 19. N1d2 Rfd8 20. Nxc5 Qxc5 21. Nf3 $16 {[%cal Gc1e3] Be3 next, and White has a big advantage.}) (18... Rc7 {natural move, but after} 19. N1d2 $18 {Black can resign.}) 19. Bf3 $5 $146 {[%cal Gf3e2] My recommendation. What is the idea? I just want to improve my pieces. Be2 will stay better than on g2. It will protect some important squares like d1 and d3.} (19. N1d2 Qc7 $3 {another computer move} (19... Rfd8 $2 20. Nf3 $1 Nf6 21. Nxc5 (21. h3 {also good, strongest for the computer} Nxe4 22. Nxc5 $16 {[%cal Gc1e3]}) 21... Qxc5 22. Be3 Qc2 {looks not clear, but after} 23. Qb1 $16 {White has the advantage.}) (19... Ne5 $2 20. Nf3 $18) 20. Nf3 Bb6 {good position for Black, for example:} 21. Qe2 a5 22. Bf4 e5 $1 $146 (22... Qc2 $2 23. Qxc2 Rxc2 24. Nbd4 $1 Rxb2 25. Bc1 $16 {[%csl Rb2]}) 23. Be3 Bxe3 24. Qxe3 Qc2 $44) 19... Ne5 20. Be2 Rfd8 {very likely move} 21. N1d2 {Now Black needs to find only move} Bd4 $1 {[%csl Gc2][%cal Gc8c2] with the idea Rc2. If not Bd4, we have a big advantage} 22. Kg2 Rc2 23. Bd1 {now Black needs to find} Rcc8 $1 24. f4 (24. Bh5 $5) 24... Nd3 $1 {only move.} 25. Qxd3 Bxb2 26. Qxd8+ Rxd8 27. Bxb2 Qe3 {only move} 28. Bc1 $13 {Without preparation, it looks that White is much better, but according to the engine it's equal.} *

