is my last try.} Bxd4 10. Nxd4 Qxd4 11. Bb2 Qd8 {Maybe we can play somehow, only 2 amateurs games.} 12. O-O {Very difficult to analyze it, but playable. Now what's the best for Black? I don't know. Nc6, Na6, Qe7 etc.} Qe7 {If White takes on b7 and f6 it's equal.} 13. Qc3 $6 {Maybe we can play more tricky.} Re8 14. Ba3 $44 {Without two pawns, but White has good compensation. For practical reasons. better to have White here, because it's not easy to play it with Black.}) (9. e3 {transposes to 9.0-0.}) 9... Nc6 ({In case of} 9... Bxd4 {I like White's position.} 10. Nxd4 Qxd4 11. Bb2 Qd8 12. Qc1 $36 {It's long play with pressure, Rd1-Nc4, a lot of ideas for play, not easy to analyze this position for our opponent.}) 10. e3 {is less forced, also you can start with 9.e3.} ({If} 10. Qc2 Nxd4 {is the idea.} 11. Nxd4 Bxd4 12. Ba3 {looks the best.} Re8 13. Nf3 {Our position looks very well, but Black can play} e5 $1 14. Rfd1 {And now the only good move} Bg4 $1 15. e3 {looks as critical, but now Black can play fantastically, you can try to find it.} (15. Bc5 $5 {Maybe it's also an option.} Qd7 {Computer move. For what?} 16. Bxd4 Bf5 {For Bf5.} 17. Qc1 {The best.} exd4 18. Rxb7 {And now} d3 $1 {Probably equal.} 19. exd3 Qa4 $11) 15... Qd5 $1 {Now White has a choice:} 16. Nd2 (16. Nxd4 {is another way.} Bxd1 17. Qxd1 (17. Rxd1 $2 {loses material.} Qa5 $15 {[%csl Ra3,Rd4]}) 17... Qxa2 18. Ra1 Qc4 19. Nf5 {Looks better for first view, but after} Rad8 20. Qe1 c5 {looks very unclear.} 21. Bxb7 $13 {I don't know for whom is better in a real game, maybe for White, maybe for Black. Difficult to say. But the position is unclear.}) 16... Qa5 17. Nc4 Bxd1 18. Rxd1 Qc3 19. Qa4 Rab8 {The best option.} 20. Bb2 b5 $1 {Only move.} 21. Bxc3 bxa4 22. exd4 exd4 23. Rxd4 {looks as equal after} Red8 $1 {It's important to change the rook on d4. You can try to play it, but I don't believe it's advantage.} 24. Rxd8+ Rxd8 25. Kf1 Rd3 $132 {could be counterplay. Must be normal for Black.}) 10... e5 11. Nxe5 {looks as slightly better for White, but after} Nxe5 12. dxe5 Bxe5 13. Nc4 Bd6 {It is unpleasant to play for Black, but I cannot say that it's advantage.} 14. Nxd6 (14. Na5 $5 {It's not so bad, but unpleasant. So understandable that there are not so many games here.}) 14... Qxd6 15. Qxd6 cxd6 16. Ba3 $14 {We can say that we are a bit better.}) 7. a3 {I prefer this line, maybe it's more interesting and we exclude the a5 line.} (7. O-O {is possible, but at the very least, Black can switch to a5 line.} a5 {see under 6...a5.}) 7... Be7 {is main.} ({If} 7... Bxd2+ {then} 8. Nxd2 {with tempo.} Nd5 9. O-O {looks more comfortable.} (9. a4 {is possible, but leads to unclear.} Bb7 10. axb5 Ne3 $5 {Interesting position. What's that?} 11. fxe3 Bxg2 12. Rg1 $13 {Bb7 or Bd5, looks playable for Black. Very complicated position.}) 9... Bb7 10. Ne4 {Nc5 is a threat.} Nd7 11. b3 $44 {Positional play. I think we can play it.}) ({If} 7... Ba5 $146 {I don't know what's that.} 8. a4 {looks logical.} a6 {We can try to play} 9. axb5 axb5 {and} 10. b4 $5 cxb3 11. O-O Bb7 {If Nb3, Bc3 is not so clear.} 12. Qxb3 $44 {Compensation for sure.}) 8. Ne5 Nd5 {Only this move was played.} (8... Qxd4 $146 {But here we have a lot of ideas.} 9. Nxf7 {Normal move.} (9. Nc6 $2 {This is the only huge mistake. You can try to find why it's bad for White.} Qb6 $1 {The best move.} 10. Nxe7 Bb7 $1 {If the pawn is on a6, White would win after} 11. Nc8 {But} Qa6 $19 {And we lost. Not immediately, but White is 2 pawns down.}) 9... Kxf7 10. Bxa8 c6 11. O-O {We will wait Black's ideas. I think it is very difficult to play, but it's not advantage.} a5 12. Nf3 {Qa7 is met with Ne5+.} Qb6 13. Bf4 {It's not easy to understand what's that, but it's very very risky for Black.} Rd8 14. Qc2 Bd7 {Only good move. Difficult to believe that White cannot win immediately, but maybe not.} 15. a4 Kg8 16. axb5 cxb5 $14 {Now White has a way out for the bishop, but only slightly better. Anyway, diffcult to expect this line. Who will play 8...Qxd4?}) 9. O-O Bb7 $5 {Serious alternative which was tried in only three games.} (9... O-O 10. b3 {This is the main position of Unit 6, and we'll discuss it in "Unit 6 part 4".}) 10. a4 {Best move.} c6 ({If} 10... a6 {we can take all.} 11. axb5 axb5 12. Rxa8 Bxa8 13. Ndxc4 {[%cal Rb5c4,Gd1a4] Slightly better for us.} f6 $146 {is a concrete line. We can play} (13... O-O 14. Na3 $14 {White won in Makarian-Dudin, 2021.}) 14. e4 $1 fxe5 15. exd5 {The knight on c4 is still not hanging.} exd4 {Maybe this move, but it looks very risky. A lot of options: Qh5, Qd4, d6. For example:} (15... Bxd5 16. Nxe5 $14) 16. Qxd4 $5 {I want to find an idea for play.} (16. Qh5+ {also looks interesting.} g6 17. Qe5 Rf8 {Only move. Again a lot of tries for White.} 18. d6 {The most forcing.} (18. Qxe6 {leads to a forced draw.} bxc4 19. Re1 Qd6 20. Qc8+ Kf7 21. Qe6+ Ke8 $11) 18... cxd6 19. Qxb5+ Nd7 20. Bh3 Kf7 21. Bh6 Re8 {Only move. Very risky position for Black.} 22. Bf4 {But computer defends it somehow. I don't know, I can't find a clear advantage, but it looks very risky.}) (16. d6 {Possible, but difficult to find advantage.} Bxg2 17. Qh5+ {Check.} g6 18. Qxb5+ {Check.} Nd7 {I can't believe that somebody could play it with Black.} 19. Kxg2 {possible, but also equal.} (19. dxe7 Qa8 {Crazy positions.} 20. Rd1 {But it is probably equal after} Bh1 21. f3 Qxf3 22. Qxd7+ Kxd7 23. Ne5+ Kxe7 24. Nxf3 $11 {Must be draw.}) 19... cxd6 20. Bf4 O-O 21. Bxd6 Bxd6 22. Nxd6 $11 {Nf6 or Qa8+ are possible.}) 16... bxc4 17. Qxg7 Bf6 $1 (17... Rf8 18. d6 {Now I think we have an advantage.} Bxg2 19. dxe7 $14 {The endgame is better for White.}) 18. Qh6 {We sacrificed the knight, but the attack continues.} Bxd5 19. Bxd5 exd5 20. Qh5+ {What's that?} Ke7 21. Re1+ Kd6 22. b3 $5 {with Ba3 idea. A sample line:} cxb3 23. Qf5 Re8 24. Bf4+ {Black's king is very brave.} Kc5 25. Rc1+ Kb4 {Very brave.} 26. Bd2+ Ka3 27. Qd3 {Super move, and I don't know for whom it's more risky.} Qd7 28. Bc3 Bxc3 29. Qxc3 {We want to mate.} Re2 {Only move.} 30. Qc5+ Kb2 {And it's draw.} (30... Ka2 $4 {loses} 31. Qa5+ Kb2 32. Qa1#) 31. Qc3+ Ka3 32. Qc5+ $11 {You can analyze more, but I don't believe this line will happen against you, it's very seldom line.}) 11. e4 {Now Black has a big choice, because all knight's moves are possible.} Nf6 {The only move played in practice, only 2 games here: Chigaev-Bluebaum and Injac-Niemann.} (11... Nb4 $146 {is possible and interesting. Maybe in 1 or 2 we will see 30 games here, but for now, no games.} 12. Qg4 O-O 13. Ndf3 {It's playable for both sides.} Kh8 {No games, as usual.} 14. Bg5 {Maybe we can try this.} (14. Ng5 $5 {is also possible, other moves also interesting. A lot of ideas. Fresh and free to analyze.}) 14... f6 15. Nh4 {Can we play for a win?} fxg5 16. Nhg6+ hxg6 17. Qh3+ Kg8 18. Qxe6+ Kh7 {Only move.} 19. Qxg6+ Kg8 {Probably draw, because if we play} 20. Bh3 g4 $1 {Position is crazy, of course.} 21. Qe6+ Kh7 22. Qg6+ $11 {if 23.Bg4 Bc8.}) (11... Nb6 $146 12. Qg4 {Important move, attacks the pawn.} O-O 13. Ndf3 {Now a lot of our pieces try to attack the king.} Kh8 14. Qh5 {I think it's interesting.} Kg8 15. h4 $40 {A lot of ideas, we can sit here for one more hour to analyze, but no need. It's a new position. I just show you ideas, because it is not practical to analyze it for 40 moves.}) (11... Nc7 $146 {also possible.} 12. Qe2 ({If you want to play forced,} 12. axb5 {you can take here and after} cxb5 13. Ndxc4 {take here. It's interesting, but what's that?} bxc4 {Necessary.} 14. Qa4+ Nd7 {The best.} (14... Kf8 {If this, White just has compensation.} 15. Rd1 $44 {The king is very bad.}) 15. Bf4 {looks interesting, Black has a lot of options.} Bf6 {Simple move.} 16. Nxc4 {is also interesting.} (16. Nxd7 {A lot of exchanges.} Qxd7 17. Bxc7 Bxd4 $11 {Probably it's equal.}) 16... O-O 17. Na5 {is the idea.} Rb8 18. Nxb7 Rxb7 19. e5 {But it's just position, no advantage after} Nd5 20. exf6 N7xf6 $11 {That's why maybe no need to play so forced.}) 12... Qxd4 13. Ndf3 Qd8 14. Rd1 {looks very good for us.} Qc8 15. Ng5 O-O 16. Nxh7 {As you see, White has a lot of tactical ideas.} Kxh7 17. Qh5+ Kg8 18. g4 $1 {And g5 and g6. Unfortunately we cannot play Ra3-Rh3, but in future who knows. Here for example, only move is} Ne8 $1 19. g5 Qc7 {Only move.} 20. g6 fxg6 21. Nxg6 Nf6 {No attack?} 22. Qh3 {We only start. A lot of questions for Black.} Nh7 $1 {Again only move.} 23. Qxe6+ Rf7 24. Ne5 Bf6 {The best.} 25. Nxf7 Qxf7 26. Qxf7+ {We can go to ending,} Kxf7 27. e5 Bxe5 28. axb5 $13 {It's not all, we can analyze it for 40 moves, but better to stop here. For sure, we have compensation.}) 12. Ndf3 {I like Chigaev's move more, for long play.} (12. Ng4 {is a possible idea, played by Injac.} Nxg4 $146 {was the best.} 13. Qxg4 Qxd4 14. Nf3 h5 $1 {Good move.} 15. Qxe6 Qxf2+ {is necessary, now White can sacrifice an exchange.} 16. Rxf2 fxe6 17. Nd4 $5 {But it leads to a balanced position.} Bc5 18. Nxe6 Bxf2+ 19. Kxf2 $13 {We can play it, maybe the opponent will make mistake, but it's balanced.}) 12... O-O 13. Ng5 $146 {We can try this maybe. For example:} Qe8 14. Ng4 Nbd7 15. e5 {If Nxg4, Qxg4 looks good for us.} Nd5 16. h4 {Very complicated position.} c5 $5 {is maybe the best.} (16... h6 17. Ne4 $36 {Big initiative for White.}) 17. axb5 {We can take a pawn, what's that?} cxd4 18. Qxd4 $36 {Interesting position, you can analyze it deeper if you want.} *

