{[%tqu "En","White has tried many moves here, what is you choice?","","","h2h4","is our recommendation, fantastic move, this is very useful in many Catalan position.",10,"c1f4","My first idea was to offer you this, but I analyzed it with Alexey and we understood that it is quite empty.",0,"c4e3","is a very funny variation, but it doesn't lead to an advantage.",0,"f1d1","Very important: We don't play Rd1, because after c5 Black has no problems.",0] [#]} 11. h4 $5 {is our recommendation, fantastic move, this is very useful in many Catalan position.} h6 12. Ne3 {Now this move is stronger.} c5 13. d5 exd5 14. e5 $1 {With the pawns back on h2 an h7, Black was absolutely fine, here it is different.} Ne8 $6 15. Rd1 Nc7 16. Nf5 Ne6 17. Bxh6 $1 $16 {We can sacrifice the piece with an advantage.} *

