{[#]} {[%tqu "En","Dubov faced this position against two very strong opponents. White to move.","","","a3e7","In the second time that Dubov faced this variation, he improved by playing 13.Bxe7.",10,"d1c1","was tried by Dubov against Yu. But later on Dubov ignored Black's strategical idea of Bxa3-b4-Nc3.",0]} 13. Bxe7 $1 {In the second time that Dubov faced this variation, he improved by playing 13.Bxe7.} (13. Rc1 {was tried by Dubov against Yu. But later on Dubov ignored Black's strategical idea of Bxa3-b4-Nc3.} c6 (13... Bd6 $1 {is the strongest move for Black, and after the typical} 14. Nd3 Na6 $1 $132 {Maybe we still have compensation, but we should be already careful not to end up in a worse position.}) 14. Nd2 $2 (14. Bxe7 $1 {was necessary tranposing to the main line.}) 14... Bxa3 $1 15. Rxa3 b4 16. Raa1 Nc3 {Black's knight on c3 is very strong. GM Dubov made a lot of mistakes, but White's position is still defendable. Of course, now we need to use our compensation to make a draw and not to win, but this shows that even if things go wrong, you can still play.}) 13... Qxe7 14. Rc1 $44 {I like the move Rc1, because the knight on b1 is still flexible, and we can decide later how to develop it.} *

