{[%evp 0,27,19,31,14,-14,-11,0,0,-14,-5,3,8,2,-17,-16,-6,-36,-42,-42,-57,-52,-24,-41,-24,-43,-5,-23,-23,-14] [#]} {[%tqu "En","This is a move that we should be prepared against, because it is not easy to figure out the best continuation without knowing the position. White to move.","","","a2a3","The last move by popularity, but the strongest one, I think.",10,"c4d5","is not interesting.",0,"d4c5","also leads to nothing.",0]} 7. a3 $1 {The last move by popularity, but the strongest one, I think.} (7. cxd5 {is not interesting.} exd5 $11) (7. dxc5 {also leads to nothing.} Bxc5 $11 {[%csl Rd2] Black has no problems, and the knight on d2 is now misplaced.}) (7. O-O {is a possible move, but not my recommendation.} cxd4 8. Nxd4 Nc6 9. Nxc6 bxc6 10. Qc2 $13 {Dubov tried to play this move, but Black is fine after many moves: e5 or a5.}) 7... Bxd2+ 8. Qxd2 {We want to be able to recapture with the queen on d4.} *

