{[%evp 0,27,19,31,14,-14,-11,0,0,-14,-5,3,8,2,-17,-16,-6,-36,-42,-42,-57,-52,-24,-41,-24,-43,-5,-23,-23,-14] [#]} {[%tqu "En","An instructive moment in the position. White to move.","","","f1d1","A very typical preparatory move, we can play e2-e4 confindently only when Black commited to b6, so that c6 is weakened.",10,"e2e4","In the game Illescas-Polgar, White rushed to play e4. But Black can equalize.",0]} 9. Rd1 {A very typical preparatory move, we can play e2-e4 confindently only when Black commited to b6, so that c6 is weakened.} (9. e4 {In the game Illescas-Polgar, White rushed to play e4. But Black can equalize.} Bxd2 10. Nxd2 Nxe4 11. Nxe4 dxe4 $11 {[%csl Rd4,Ye8][%cal Gg2e4,Gd7f6,Yc2e4,Ye6e5] And now White doesn't have a good recapture.}) 9... Qe7 10. a3 Bd6 11. Re1 $5 {[%csl Re7] Another tricky move, we follow Black's queen.} *

